- loan_id now reserved via AppStateManager.getNextLoanId(); creating a
  loan after deletions or restores can no longer collide with an
  existing ID. Loan creation is logged to the canonical
  AppState.transactions and derived totals are recalculated on
  acceptance. (F-09/F-06)
- Both start-year derivations use Calculations.resolveScheduleStartYear
  — a December loan with a January start month schedules into the next
  year instead of eleven months into the past.
- Remaining hardcoded rates (12% initiation on stockvel excess, 10%
  per-month minimum, R60 admin and its stockvel-variable form) read
  Calculations.RATES / the shared admin rule. (F-07/F-16)
- Client name and account number escaped in the results panel;
  sanitize.js loaded. (F-04)
- 16 verbose logs gated behind DEBUG. (F-17)
